The PackageExpander_Recovers_WhenFileIsLocked unit test has the following assert which is supposed to ensure that InstallFromSourceAsync throws an IOException. It is not throwing an exception, however the test still passes (no assert).

`Func<CancellationToken, Task<bool>> action = (ct) =>
{
    Assert.ThrowsAnyAsync<IOException>(async () =>
                                await PackageExtractor.InstallFromSourceAsync(
                                    identity,
                                    packageDownloader,
                                    versionFolderPathResolver,
                                    packageExtractionContext,
                                    token));
     return Task.FromResult(true);
};`

I discovered this in release-6.0.x where error VSTHRD110 instructed me to change the code to the following:

`Func<CancellationToken, Task<bool>> action = async (ct) =>
                        {
                            await Assert.ThrowsAnyAsync<IOException>(() =>
                                PackageExtractor.InstallFromSourceAsync(
                                    identity,
                                    packageDownloader,
                                    versionFolderPathResolver,
                                    packageExtractionContext,
                                    token));
                            return true;
                        };`

After making this change, the assert started failing the test which is correct.

